  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study examining the influence of viscosity and rotational speed on the relative hemolysis index was conducted informally during model development; results confirmed low parametric sensitivity across the operating envelope and supported the MRL 2 classification. This screening activity is documented in the project technical report but has not been linked as a structured SensitivityAnalysis node in the present package.",
