    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. Validation results demonstrate NIH prediction accuracy within the 15% acceptance band at all five COU operating points, yielding RH < 1 at all conditions. The informal screening sensitivity study, documented in the project technical report, confirmed low parametric sensitivity of the hemolysis index to key input variations, providing additional confidence in the nominal-input simulation strategy. The overall body of evidence is judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision for the Class II CPB device.",
